      <body>Yaroslav, the code you cited refers to activesupport/lib/active_support/inflector.rb which is not affected by the patch.

The purpose of this ticket is to allow
@@@ ruby
some_string.parameterize(&quot;_&quot;)
# instead of
&quot;La, la, la!&quot;.parameterize.dasherize
# or
ActiveSupport::Inflector.parameterize &quot;La, la, la!&quot;, &quot;_&quot;
@@@


Would anyone consider applying if I rebase the patch against master?</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Yaroslav, the code you cited refers to
activesupport/lib/active_support/inflector.rb which is not affected
by the patch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of this ticket is to allow&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;
some_string.parameterize(&amp;quot;_&amp;quot;)
# instead of
&amp;quot;La, la, la!&amp;quot;.parameterize.dasherize
# or
ActiveSupport::Inflector.parameterize &amp;quot;La, la, la!&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;_&amp;quot;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would anyone consider applying if I rebase the patch against
master?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
